&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A hashing function is a mathematical algorithm that converts an input (or &amp;ldquo;message&amp;rdquo;) into a fixed-size string of bytes, typically a hash code or hash value. This output is usually a short, unique representation of the input data. Examples of common hash functions include MD5, SHA-1, and SHA-256.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
